"title": "5909: motives, importance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5909: motives, importance of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God acts from the highest, purest motives and expects his people to do the same.</p>\n<h2>God's supreme motive is the honour of his name</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:8\">PSA 106:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:16\">EXO 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:3\">PSA 23:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:7\">ISA 43:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:20-Ezek36:23\">EZK 36:20–36:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:11–1:14</a></p>\n<h2>God's glory is to be the highest motive of his people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:31\">1CO 10:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:7-Num25:13\">NUM 25:7–25:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:8\">ISA 26:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:17\">COL 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:11\">1PE 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Purity of motive is essential for acceptable worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:1-Matt6:18\">MAT 6:1–6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:6\">PSA 51:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:10\">PSA 51:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:11\">PSA 86:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:8\">MAT 5:8</a></p>\n<h2>Wrong motives hinder effective prayer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:3\">JAS 4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps66:18\">PSA 66:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:21-1John3:22\">1JN 3:21–3:22</a></p>\n<h2>Motives for good moral behaviour</h2>\n<h3>Wanting to please God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:22-Col3:25\">COL 3:22–3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:5-Eph6:8\">EPH 6:5–6:8</a></p>\n<h3>Compassion for others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:17-Deut24:22\">DEU 24:17–24:22</a></strong> <em>The experience of slavery and the exodus were to promote compassion for the poor and the alien.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod22:21-Exod22:27\">EXO 22:21–22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:35-Lev25:42\">LEV 25:35–25:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:54-Lev25:55\">LEV 25:54–25:55</a></p>\n<h3>Fear of punishment for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:4\">HEB 13:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5-Col3:6\">COL 3:5–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:3-1Thess4:6\">1TH 4:3–4:6</a></p>\n<h2>God judges the motives of the heart</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:2\">PRO 16:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:27\">PRO 20:27</a></p>",
